For example, in the desert you fall into a sandstorm, which is significantly lowering visibility.
On the other hand, the mountains need to be careful to avoid falling under the lawn.
The individual races are pretty well arranged.
There are only a few varieties, but that's enough.
For a while, you are trying to get some of the rivals, and then you try to improve your time (the standard racing with the second-time) or you compete with one opponent.
Besides all the other things, you have a time-only contact with the police that makes your task even more difficult.
The components outside the car are new.
It's just an interactive animation where most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help him by pressing the buttons at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
Although it is surprising that these fragments are much less than you could expect (only three to be precise).
In fact, it turns out that it is good for the game because it is not boring; given all the above, it is one of the things that make the game more interesting.
The race model is followed by previous models.
This means that she is no longer a special one, but that cannot be considered a deficiency.
If you're looking for a real life imitation, you'll have to find somewhere else.
Nevertheless, this driving model is very good for dynamic races, although better options can be found on the market.
So far, it's very good.
However, some time after that, problems begin.
Unlike the driving model, the model of collision is not that good.
You don't expect difficult conversions and collisions from this game, but if you have no idea how your car will behave, something is wrong.
Usually, by running or driving past the cars in a dense stream, you sometimes touch another machine, but sometimes in a practically similar situation, your car starts freaking off.
Or it's breaking up.
This is not so important because of the restart system, but it's enough to ruin fun.
The restarts are built so that if you break or go far off the route, the game returns you to the point where it has been interrupted.
However, only five restarts are available for each race.
If you use them all, you'll have to start the race from the beginning.
